Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
foreach_in_collection(25.10)                      foreach_in_collection(25.10)

Name
       foreach_in_collection  -  Iterates through all objects in the specified
       collection and executes the commands in the specified script body

Syntax
       foreach_in_collection

       [-help]

       <var_name><collection><body>

       Iterates through all objects in the specified collection  and  executes
       the commands in the specified script body.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       <body> Specifies  the  script of commands to execute during each itera-
              tion.

       <collection>
              Specifies the collection of objects through which to iterate.

       <var_name>
              Specifies  the  iterator  variable.   During   each   iteration,
              <var_name>  is  set  to  a collection of exactly one object. Any
              command that accepts collections  can  accept  <var_name>  as  a
              value.

Examples
              * The following command prints out the hierarchical names of all
                the cells in a design:

                foreach_in_collection iCell [get_cells *] {

                puts "Cell = [get_property $iCell hierarchical_name]"

                }

                Cell = ck_0

                Cell = ck_1

                Cell = ck_2

                Cell = ck_4

              * The  following  example  shows a more complex use of the fore-
                ach_in_collection command:

                set cellCollection [get_cells temp1_reg]

                set libCellCollection [get_lib_cells -of_objects  $cellCollec-
                tion]

                set libArc [get_lib_arcs -of_objects $libCellCollection]

                foreach_in_collection arc $libArc {

                set fpin [get_property $arc from_lib_pin]

                set tpin [get_property $arc to_lib_pin]

                set sense [get_property $arc timing_type]

                set from_pin_name [get_property $fpin name]

                set to_pin_name [get_property $tpin name]

                puts  [format "%25s -> %25s %-20s" $from_pin_name $to_pin_name
                $sense]}

